article.description: Julie Wojta had 20 points and 11 rebounds, Kayla Tetschlag added 17 points and No. 17 Wisconsin-Green Bay remained unbeaten with a 74-53 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Saturday.
article.headline: Wis.-Green Bay extends Horizon League win streak to 35 games
article.linkText: Green Bay remains unbeaten, extends streak
article.story:
MILWAUKEE, Wis. -- Julie Wojta had 20 points and 11 rebounds, Kayla Tetschlag added 17 points and No. 17 Wisconsin-Green Bay remained unbeaten with a 74-53 victory over Wisconsin-Milwaukee on Saturday.

The Phoenix (16-0, 5-0) overcame a cold shooting first half to remain among four undefeated teams in Division I women's basketball. The win extended the school's Horizon League winning streak to 35 games.

Green Bay struggled shooting during the first half, at one point missing 10 straight from the field. In all, Green Bay hit just 12 of 29 shots in the first half.

The Phoenix broke the game open at the beginning of the second half, using an 18-6 run to grab a 55-33 lead with 11:59 remaining. The Panthers got no closer than 16 the rest of the way.

Milwaukee (6-10, 1-4) was led by Lindsay Laur with 17 points and Ashley Imperiale with 16.
